cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the evaluation of research organizations based on a subset of their scientific production, which is a topic related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of proportional functions to determine the size of the subset is also related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the analysis of variations in ranking due to changes in the subset size could also be relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
